what does this command do: ssh -i "~/UserKey.pem" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com
This is a complex SSH configuration that will allow you to access your EC2 instance from the local machine on port 590.  The command specifies an identity file, which must be placed in ~/UserKey/.pem and also uses -C for compression of the encrypted data stream between machines (which can improve performance). The connection is then forwarded locally through a tunnel using SSH's dynamic port forwarding feature (-L) to forward traffic on local machine port 5903 directly to your EC2 instance running on localhost:590.
